Devolution CS Mwangi Kiunjuri has said that the Cabinet Secretaries have a right to campaign for the Jubilee government's re-election.Kiunjuri said there is nothing wrong in supporting the government of the day.&ldquo;Nothing stops us from campaigning for President Uhuru Kenyatta and his deputy William Ruto. We shall ensure the Jubilee government is re-elected,&rdquo; he said.At the same time, the CS urged those who will lose in the nominations to accept defeat and support the winners.&ldquo;Whoever will lose should accept that there is tomorrow. I also lost at one time and accepted defeat. We know the opposition will never accept defeat but this time they must accept and move on,&rdquo; he said.He was speaking on Sunday at Giakanja trading centre in Tetu, Nyeri during the local volleyball tournament.He also emphasized the need to improve sporting activities in the area to tap local talents.The youth were also told to ensure they vote for leaders of integrity.